(44, 1, 'ORANGE BLOOD', '&lt;p&gt;A blood orange is a citrus organic product that appears to be like an orange all things considered yet has dark red shaded leafy foods. The red shading is the consequence of anthocyanin, which creates when these citrus natural products mature during warm days tempered with cooler evenings.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Blood oranges are better than different oranges. Their juice is flavorful, but since it is significantly better than great squeezed orange, it ages rapidly and ought to be utilized or smashed that day it\'s squeezed.\r\n&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Nutritional facts&lt;/b&gt;:1 orange blood fruit (140g) provides following\r\nnutrition:&lt;/p&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;ul&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Calories: 69&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Fat: 0.2&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Carbohydrates: 18g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Fiber: 3.1g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Protein: 1.3g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Benefits&lt;/b&gt;: Apart from being rich in vitamin C, blood oranges also offer unique health benefits associated with high levels of anthocyanins. Anthocyanins are red flavonoid pigments that give the blood oranges their intense color and wondrous antioxidant properties. Nutritionists believe that anthocyanins have anti-inflammatory properties that help prevent cancer, bacterial infections, diabetes and reduce the risk of heart disease. They also help defend blood vessels from oxidative damage and reduce the accumulation of LDL cholesterol. &lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Variable weight&lt;/b&gt;: Kindly note all the fresh fruits and vegetables are billed based on exact weight during order processing, in case if the weight exceeds the requested weight by 5% more then you will be charged for 5% excess weight.\r\n&lt;/p&gt;', '', 'ORANGE BLOOD ', '', ''),
