(71, 1, 'THAI TAMARIND', '&lt;p&gt;Tamarind is one of the staple fixings utilized in Thai Cuisine,\r\nalongside chili, lemongrass and Lime. The fruit is generally circulated in a\r\nTamarind Paste, which is utilized in various Thai curries. The Tamarind is\r\nnormally dried with or without seeds and afterward stuffed and sold as a\r\npaste on business sectors and markets.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Nutritional facts&lt;/b&gt;: 120g of raw tamarind consist of following nutritional\r\nfacts:\r\n\r\n&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Calories: 287&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Fat: 0.7g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Carbohydrates: 75g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Fiber: 6.1g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Sugar: 46.6g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n  &lt;li&gt;Protein: 3.4g&lt;/li&gt;\r\n&lt;/ul&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Benefits&lt;/b&gt;: Tamarind pulp contains plant compounds that may protect\r\nagainst heart disease and oxidative damage. Several studies show that\r\ntamarind can combat many different microbes. It may help kill bacteria,\r\nviruses, fungi and parasites. There are several ways to enjoy tamarind. It\r\ncan be used in sweet and savory dishes, or eaten straight from the pod.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Variable weight&lt;/b&gt;: Kindly note all the fresh fruits and vegetables are billed\r\nbased on exact weight during order processing, in case if the weight\r\nexceeds the requested weight by 5% more then you will be charged for 5%\r\nexcess weight.&lt;/p&gt;', '', 'THAI TAMARIND', '', ''),
